items.title: Cubs' 6th straight win has Cards 6 back
items.summary: Kyle Schwarber hit his 27th home run and Jason Heyward smacked a clutch tiebreaking RBI single with two outs in the seventh inning to lift the Cubs to their sixth straight win, a 4-3 victory Sunday over the Cardinals.
items.content: Kyle Schwarber hit his 27th home run and Jason Heyward smacked a clutch tiebreaking RBI single with two outs in the seventh inning to lift the Cubs to their sixth straight win, a 4-3 victory Sunday over the Cardinals.

items.title: Harper shows MVP form in pregame BP
items.summary: Bryce Harper took batting practice at Nationals Park on Sunday, unleashing his violent swing on the field for the first time since his knee injury last month.
